    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-07T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-07T02:00:00-05:00" n="326"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d326">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.91293/21: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-07T14:00:00+07:00"
                            >April 7, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 9—9:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>622. Reliably informed that British correspondent who threatened to expose
                    Votaw’s background if latter should represent AP on Yenan trip (Embassy’s 556,
                    March 30 and Department’s 421, April 1, 10 a.m. [<hi rend="italic">p.m.</hi>]
                    expressed to Moosa, local AP correspondent, strong criticism of such choice and
                    that Moosa has now canceled Votaw’s appointment as AP representative on trip.
                    Votaw will probably make trip as representative of “other organizations”.</p>
                <p>Foregoing confirmed indirectly by Moosa who has informed officer of Embassy
                    [that] Yenan trip too long for regular AP staff member but that while Votaw only
                    available person to represent AP his connection with Information Ministry makes
                    him unsuitable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
